Library Book Counter Using Static Variable
Develop a Java program to track the total number of books added to a library. Use a static variable to maintain the count and display the count whenever a new book is added.
Sample Input
Books Added: 3
Sample Output
Book Added
Total Books: 1

Book Added
Total Books: 2

Book Added
Total Books: 3

Coding...:

import java.util.*;
class library{
    static int total=0;
    library(int n){
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            total+=1;     //increment book count
        System.out.println("Book Added");
        System.out.println("Total Books:"+total);
        }
    }
}
public class Main{
    public static void main(String agrs[]){
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();  //getting input
        library l=new library(n);//calling of constructor
    }
}
